<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 3:40PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Pike and
southeastern Montgomery Counties through 430 PM CDT...
At 340 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Linwood, or 11 miles north of Troy, moving south at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Troy, Banks, Linwood, Kent, Ansley, Troy Municipal Airport, Troy
University, China Grove, Sandfield, Currys and Orion.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
